Activity Name: Bike to hike to snowshoe - Swiftcurrent Mountain

Description: Broke my shift lever and had to bike up 1500 feet in 3rd gear. Quite an unpleasant and embarrassing climb...
Christmas in July! Not my first time getting caught in a snowstorm on July 1st...
To anyone who wants to re-create this route: bring a diaper, you're gonna need one.
Oh how I love when my $*** watch loses signal!
Watch malfunctioned  should be about 15 miles.
Should have brought that diaper again...
Class 5 mosquitos and flies. Literally made every moment unbearable. May have been the most unpleasant day in the mountains of my life. I am shocked I survived.
7 summits in 5 days. Summer is here!

Activity Name: Red Crow, Calf Robe, Unnamed peak
Description: Saw 2 mountain lions, one of which literally tried to eat me, and a moose.
The Bitterroot doesn't disappoint... She's still there, as strong as ever, full of brushy blowdown and knee deep creek crossings, ticks, toe stubbings, and a near complete lack of scenery.
